332	    /**
333	     * Invalidate the public read cache so a subsequent `getSiteContent`
334	     * re-reads the bucket. Called by the editor's publish action so a publish
335	     * is visible with no redeploy and without waiting out the TTL (D3,
336	     * `make-operations-idempotent` — busting an already-empty cache is a no-op).
337	     * When no refresh is already in flight a publish is visible on the very
338	     * next read; otherwise it is visible within the documented staleness window
339	     * — `invalidate` only expires the entry, it does not pre-empt an in-flight
