 40	 * The `/admin/content` editor (CMS plan sub-commit C5).
 41	 *
 42	 * It edits the one bilingual `SiteContent` document over three sections —
 43	 * conferences, team, translations — and persists via `Storage`:
 44	 *   - **Save draft** writes `content/site.draft.json` (private to admin);
 45	 *   - **Publish** writes `content/site.json`, removes the draft, and **busts the
 46	 *     `Content` read cache** so the change is live on the next public read with
 47	 *     NO redeploy (D3);
 48	 *   - per-image **Upload** stores the raw bytes under `images/uploads/…` and
 49	 *     rewrites the targeted `…key` field to the new bucket object key (the
 50	 *     resize/WebP/thumbnail pipeline is deferred — CMS plan §"Non-goals").
 51	 *
 52	 * The merge-onto-current-document strategy (`~/lib/content/admin-form`) means the
 53	 * form only carries the fields it renders; every unedited deep field (long bios,
 54	 * `Option` registration windows, image keys) survives, and the merged result is
 55	 * Schema-decoded at the single boundary before it is stored
 56	 * (`boundary-discipline`, `make-impossible-states-unrepresentable`).
 57	 */
 58	
 59	// `encodeDocument` yields the encoded object the React view renders from the
 60	// loader's `AdminContent`. The merge/decode/re-encode/store choreography now
 61	// lives in `DraftEditor`; the route only encodes for display.
 62	const encodeDocument = Schema.encodeUnknownEffect(SiteContent);
